<FIRST>r a PM-Nielsens     08-09 0358</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Nielsens,0368</SECOND>
<HEAD>ABC's `Roseanne' Takes First in Television Ratings</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Summer reruns, topped by the ABC comedy hit
``Roseanne,'' beat out original programming in the latest Nielsen
ratings.
   Two other ABC shows _ ``Wonder Years'' and ``Who's the Boss'' _
were next in the ratings for the week ended Aug. 6, but the network
remained in third place. ABC and NBC each finished the week with
four shows in the Top 10, but it was NBC which gained a 59th
consecutive victory.
   ``Roseanne,'' snubbed last week in the Emmy nominations,
supplanted NBC's ``Cheers'' in the top spot. The Boston barroom
antics fell to fourth place, tying with ABC's ``Coach.''
   Original programming fared poorly in the ratings, despite coming
amid summer doldrums.
   The NBC news program ``Yesterday, Today &amp; Tomorrow'' made its
debut in a tie for 19th place with ABC's ``Full House.'' ABC's
much-touted ``PrimeTime Live'' was in 37th place.
   The NBC summer series ``13 East'' dropped from 10th place last
week to 35th. Another NBC summer show, ``Knight &amp; Daye,'' remained
in the middle of the ratings in a four-way tie for 50th place.
   Fox Broadcasting Co.'s summertime jump in the ratings has
apparently bottomed out. ``Married ... With Children'' dropped to
38th place, ``Totally Hidden Video'' was 46th and ``America's Most
Wanted'' in the four-way tie for 50th place.
   NBC won the A.C. Nielsen Co. survey with an average of 10.5. CBS
was second with 9.4 and ABC third with 9.2.
   For the season to date, from Sept. 19, NBC had 14.7, ABC 11.8
and CBS 11.7. The ratings are the percentage of the 90.4 million
homes with televisions in the United States. The share is the
percentage of sets in use.
   Here are the Top 10: ABC's ``Roseanne,'' ABC's ``Wonder Years,''
ABC's ``Who's the Boss?,'' NBC's ``Cheers '' and ABC's ``Coach''
tied, NBC's ``Golden Girls,'' NBC's ``Perry Mason: The Case of the
Lost Love'' and CBS' ``Murder, She Wrote'' tied, NBC's ``Empty
Nest'' and CBS' ``Designing Women'' tied.
   ABC claimed first place among the nightly news shows. The
ratings: ABC 9.4, CBS 9.1, NBC 8.6.
</TEXT>
