<SECOND>PM-BRF--Norway-Newspaper Proposal,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Norwegian Proposes Marriage in Newspaper Headline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FREDRIKSTAD, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Egil Syversen proposed marriage to
Tonje Kolle, using the entire front page of the local newspaper to
do it.
   Syversen, a city official, was asked in an interview by the
newspaper Demokraten when he last surprised his girlfriend.
   ``I'll do it right now by asking her to marry me,'' replied
44-year-old Syversen. ``Will you marry me, Tonje?''
   The newspaper helped Syversen pop the question on Friday by
filling its front page with his picture and the headline, ``Tonje,
Should We Get Married?'' Syversen said in a telephone interview
that he knew his spur of the moment proposal would be printed, but
``that front-page headline left me speechless.''
   Surprised but not speechless, Ms. Kolle said yes, in the Monday
edition of a competing newspaper.

</TEXT>
