<FIRST>r a PM-DaughterShot     08-09 0324</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Daughter Shot,0333</SECOND>
<HEAD>Family Bought Freezer Before Shooting Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESTLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A father and daughter accused of trying
to kill a younger, 360-pound daughter to put an end to the woman's
medical bills bought a freezer to hold the body one day before the
shooting, police say.
   Valentine Kwiatkowski, 78, and his daughter Carol are charged
with assault with intent to murder, accused of twice shooting
32-year-old Anna Kwiatkowski in the head Sunday. The woman was
listed in serious condition today.
   The two suspects have told people ``they were going to put Anna
in the freezer,'' said police Sgt. Jerry Wright.
   An unidentified appliance salesman told today's Detroit News
that the two suspects bought a freezer Saturday.
   ``They came in here bopping around, and it was funny how fast
they bought it,'' the salesman said. ``I asked him if he was a
hunter. But he said he needed it because he wanted to store some
extra meat.''
   The Kwiatkowskis gave police a receipt for a 16-cubic-foot
freezer chest to be delivered this week, authorities said.
   Wright said the purchase casts doubt on the father and
daughter's reported claim to hospital staff that they planned
suicide after shooting the woman.
   Authorities said the two, who were jailed on $50,000 bail, took
Ms. Kwiatkowski to St. Joseph Mercy Hospital in Ann Arbor two hours
after the shooting. She was able to walk into the emergency room,
staff said.
   Police said Ms. Kwiatkowski was shot with a .32-caliber handgun
because of high medical bills run up by her asthma and her obesity.
   Art Torikian, a retired sheriff's detective who lives across the
street in the Detroit suburb, said Carol Kwiatkowski feuded with
neighbors and said the woman sometimes chased her father up the
street while yelling obscenities.
   ``No, I guess it isn't a surprise,'' another neighbor, Evelyn
Fagan, said of the shooting. ``The father and older sister wanted
to keep her under their control.''
</TEXT>
