<FIRST>u a PM-JetlinerBaby     08-09 0265</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Jetliner Baby,0273</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Sent to Jail For Abandoning Newborn in Jetliner</HEAD>
<DATELINE>REDWOOD CITY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was sentenced to six months
in jail today for abandoning her newborn daughter in a jetliner
bathroom.
   Christina LoCasto, 24, of New York City pleaded no contest May
25 to felony child endangerment in a plea bargain promising her no
more than a year in jail. She could have received six years in
prison if convicted.
   Authorities said Mrs. LoCasto secretly gave birth on a United
Airlines DC-10 in 1988 before the plane left Newark, N.J., and
stuffed the baby in the trash.
   The child, named Alyssa, was found after the plane landed in San
Francisco. Mrs. LoCasto turned herself in the next day.
   Superior Court Judge Margaret Kemp rejected a plea for probation
from Mrs. LoCasto's lawyer and the Probation Department. In
addition to sending her to jail in New York City, he placed her on
2{ years' probation and fined her about $800.
   Prosecutor Stephen Wagstaffe told the judge Mrs. LoCasto should
go to jail. ``Any consideration of keeping the family together
ought to be outweighed by the danger she created for the child,''
he said.
   The judge said it appeared LoCasto simply wanted the baby to
``go away.'' She said she found it hard to believe the infant had
survived the ordeal.
   Mrs. LoCasto's husband, Louis LoCasto, told authorities the
couple had been having marital problems when Alyssa was conceived
and he had no idea his wife was pregnant.
   The child is in the custody of her grandparents in New York City.
</TEXT>
