<HEAD>Bystanders Applaud Drug Bust</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDLAND, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 100 bystanders appaluded police who
led five suspected drug dealers in handcuffs from a fortresslike
home.
   ``I was concerned at first that they were going to get unruly.
But instead, they applauded when we brought the suspects out,''
said District Attorney Theresa Ferris-Dukovich.
   ``The neighbors were happy to see us doing something about the
suspected operation. I believe the house was perceived as a menace
to the neighborhood,'' she said.
   County detectives and state police with guns drawn Tuesday night
surrounded the home of Alan P. Jakes, 29, and his wife, Christine,
25. The officers scaled a 6-foot electronic fence and broke through
a steel door with a sledgehammer.
   Police said they confiscated cash, four cars, loaded weapons,
more than 4 ounces of suspected cocaine, one-fourth ounce of
suspected marijuana, and drug paraphernalia.
   The Jakes and three other people were jailed on drug charges
under $250,000 bail each.
