<FIRST>r a AM-MolesterKilled     08-09 0283</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Molester Killed,0292</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Who Confessed to Child Molestation Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHRISTIANA, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Mennonite who voluntarily confessed to
fellow worshipers that he had molested several children was fatally
shot by his 24-year-old son, state police said.
   The body of Gerard James Engel, 47, was found in his living room
Tuesday morning with a single wound to the head-neck area, police
said. Hours later state police arrested Perry Michael Engel of Gap.
   The son was arraigned before District Justice Arden I. Kopp on a
charge of homicide and jailed without bail. Police would not
comment Wednesday on a motive or on any criminal investigation of
the father.
   A mother of two children who allegedly were molested said a
state trooper was investigating the reports last week.
   Engel's employer, David Glick of Atglen Gas Service, said
Engel's youngest son, Eric, 12, telephoned him Tuesday morning.
   ``He said, `Dad won't be at work today.' I asked him if his
father was sick. Finally he told me that someone had shot his
father.
   ``He said he hadn't called an ambulance or the police. So I
dialed the 911 number and asked for an ambulance,'' Glick said.
   In the arrest warrant affidavit, Eric Engel told state police
that his brother, Perry, arrived at the home Tuesday morning,
shotgun in hand.
   The 12-year-old told police that as he walked out of the living
room _ leaving Perry and Gerard Engel alone _ the shooting occurred.
   A unidentified church leader was quoted in the Lancaster New Era
newspaper Wednesday as saying that about three weeks ago, Engel
voluntarily confessed to sexually molesting several children.
   Engel was excommunicated, the church leader said, and taken
later to a psychiatrist.
</TEXT>
