<FIRST>a e BC-APArts:Oz-Statistics Adv11-13   08-09 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-AP Arts: Oz-Statistics, Adv 11-13,0205</SECOND>
<HEAD>$Adv11</HEAD>
<HEAD>$Adv12</HEAD>
<HEAD>$Adv13</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Weekend Editions, Aug 11-13 and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-AP Arts: Wizard of Oz</HEAD>
<HEAD>The Oz Files: Statistics for 50-year-old Movie Classic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some facts and figures for ``The
Wizard of Oz,'' which celebrates its 50th anniversary this month.
   _ Cost of production: $2,777,000.
   _ Total gross from theaters: $4.8 million.
   _ Total gross from television (to 1983): $13 million.
   _ Shooting schedule: 22 weeks.
   _ Number of directors: 3 (Richard Thorpe, Victor Fleming and
King Vidor).
   _ Number of writers: 10 (three with screen credit).
   _ Judy Garland's salary: $500 a week.
   _ Ray Bolger's salary: $3,000 a week.
   _ Jack Haley's salary: $3,000 a week.
   _ Bert Lahr's salary: $2,500 a week.
   _ Number of midgets employed: 124.
   _ Toto's breed: Cairn Terrier.
   _ Toto's salary: $125 a week.
   _ Number of actors: 600.
   _ Number of costumes: 1,000.
   _ Number of Oscars: Two (Herbert Stothart for musical score, and
``Over the Rainbow'' for song).
   _ Videocassette sales (US): 600,000.
   _ Running Time: 100 minutes.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Weekend Editions, Aug. 11-13</NOTE>
