<SECOND>PM-Xerox Self-Tender,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Xerox Buys $785 Million Worth of Its Own Stock</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Xerox Corp. says it will pay $68 per
share to buy back about 11.5 million shares of its own stock, for a
total of $785 million.
   The shares represent about 11 percent of the 103 million Xerox
common shares outstanding.
   Xerox had announced the self-tender offer July 11, and said at
the time it was willing to pay between $62 and $70 per share to buy
about 11.2 million shares of common stock. The company is paying
for the shares with proceeds from a new issue of convertible
preferred stock.
   Xerox spokesman Thomas Abbott said Tuesday the stock repurchase
and the formation of the employee stock option plan won't affect
the company's financial position.
