<FIRST>r f BC-HarveyPublications     08-09 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Harvey Publications,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Harvey Publications Sold</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Harvey Publications Inc., which owns the rights
to a number of classic cartoon and comic book characters including
Casper, the Friendly Ghost, has been sold for an undisclosed price,
it was announced Wednesday.
   The family-owned New York-based concern, which publishes comic
books and has a library of 248 film cartoons from the 1950s and
1960s, is being sold to HMH Communications Inc., a company headed
by Jeffrey A. Montgomery, described in a news release as a
25-year-old entrepreneur from Los Angeles.
   Montgomery said he planned to create and produce half-hour
television cartoon series based on the Harvey characters and
increase the publication of Harvey's comic books.
   Among the other Harvey characters are Richie Rich, ``the Poor
Little Rich Boy,'' Baby Huey, Little Audrey and Little Dot.
   Harvey Publications was founded in 1940 by Alfred Harvey.
Montgomery said he approached the Harvey family about buying the
company.
</TEXT>
